MESSAGE.value: Dumping the output guesses as they are made by humans. Still need to write tutorials for CoNLL before I can actually launch these stupid tasks.
Making minor piping changes to facciliate writing logs of decision making behavior.
Added support for YAML tutorial, also added intro slide and cheat-sheet.
Getting everything all buttoned up. Still need to fix turn-in button, but otherwise we are ready to go with NER. Scary stuff.
Final idiot check passed. Gonna try a real run.
Minorly fixing bugs and removing issues.
Seem to have most bugs worked out. Ready for another run, I think.
Simulations now draw samples from the true distribution of tired turkers. This means that we're going to get correct, if pessimistic, results.
CRF now adds human observation factors based on observed human distribution. Engine has access to both error and delay distributions, which are configurable. Refactored distribution locations.
Added an overall F1 and per class F1 to get a better handle on performance.
Making ThresholdHeuristic much more aggressive, running with a huge pool of workers, seeing what happens.
Added cacheing, stubbed out MCTS, etc
Lookahead one heuristic seems to work well, if horrendously slowly.
Adding non-stupid NER features. Still need lemmas.
Put in a logistic external model stream, piped both sentiment and person id to it. Still needs an actual model.
Slight refactoring
Getting LogisticRegression working for person and sentiment.
Have an EM system in, with a baby standalone test, though I'm not sure exactly what behavior to expect, so I can't tell if it's totally working.
Online EM implemented, but with bogus gradients...
Online EM seems now to be fixed!!!!! And there was much rejoicing.
Reworked EM to be a less redundant implementation, by adding some horrible type hacks.
Setting everything up to run experiments by sampling from past real human observations. This is basically excellent. Sentiment and NER are both ready to cook.
Insanely poor formatting, but starting to put in results section
Making a better results section
Added means to get socher's output vectors for the sentiment task, so we have better features to use for learning, so maybe we just win all the things on accuracy and cost.
